   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1862_02_04_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Bourjau_Hubener_Shanghai_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>Per Spray<lb/>Shanghai, 4th Feb. 1862.<lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler +
                Co.<lb/>Nagasaki<lb/> With reference to our last letter from 21st/25th<lb/>of last
                month we notify you of our <lb/> receiving your esteemed letter from 23rd Jan.,
                which<lb/>we recived this morning by means of “Horatio”.<lb/>The £1,500 instructed
                for Mr. Morf<lb/>have been passed to him at a rate of 6/2½ d with <lb/> Ts
                4,832.2.2. Kindly excuse that we <lb/> omitted to provide you with this
                information<lb/> at the end of our letter of 21st Jan. <lb/>Because of New Year
                business here, too,<lb/> has been resting entirely for the last 8 days,<lb/> the
                only news we can tell you about the <lb/> market here is that stone
                coal⅌[?]<lb/>“Bar. F. van Dambenoy” shall be sold for <lb/> Ts 9. Arrivals of ships
                remain rare and, <lb/>because Americ. vessels are hard to charter, <lb/>for as long
                as the differences between North America <lb/>and England have not been settled
                peacefully, cargoes <lb/>will at least remain at their current level<lb/> or even
                rise. – The next ship to go there <lb/>will probably be the Armistici.<lb/>We
                sign<lb/> respectfully and devotedly<lb/> Bourjau Hubener + Co.<lb/>Ernst Behre</p>
         <pb facs="1862_02_04_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Bourjau_Hubener_Shanghai_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <pb facs="1862_02_04_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Bourjau_Hubener_Shanghai_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <pb facs="1862_02_04_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Bourjau_Hubener_Shanghai_4.tif" n="4"/>
         <p>⟨1862<lb/>Shanghai 4th Feb.<lb/>Bourjau Hübener &amp; Co.<lb/>r[eceived]/ 12/2
                62<lb/>a[nswered]/14/2 62⟩<lb/>
         </p>
      </body>
